If a foreign student is caught doing illegal part-time work in China, they may be subject to fines and/or other penalties. 

According to the recent regulations of the People's Republic of China on the Administration of Employment of Foreigners ("the Regulations"), foreign students who engage in illegal employment during their study period may be subject to the following penalties:

1. They may be fined up to RMB 5,000 yuan (approximately USD 770);
2. Their part-time work permit may be terminated; 
3. Their student visa may be cancelled;
4. They may face legal penalties such as deportation and a temporary or permanent ban on entry into China.

It's important for foreign students to follow the regulations to avoid such penalties during their study period in China.
